==============================================================================================================
  SECTION D — BEHAVIORAL ANOMALY DETECTION: EWMA (Base System)
==============================================================================================================

  EWMA tracks per-user activity rate across 8 time windows.
  Activity Rate r_t = 3600 / (t_current - t_last)  [actions per hour]
  EWMA_new = λ × r_t + (1-λ) × EWMA_old   where λ = 0.3

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  EVENT-001  |  2026-04-13 11:31:00  |  USR001 (Ayesha Khan)
  Action      : PERM_CHECK  |  File: source_code_v3.py
  Gap since last action : 383s  →  r_t = 3600/383 = 9.399 actions/hr
  EWMA Update (1h window):  λ×9.399 + (1-λ)×4.1
             = 0.3×9.399 + 0.7×4.1
             = 2.8197 + 2.87 = 5.6897
  Deviation from baseline: |9.399 - 4.1| / 4.1 = 1.2921
  ✓  Normal activity — EWMA updated
